        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "{{Zend_Db_Select}}'s {{union()}} method does not follow the docs specifications, it just returns {{$this}} if the {{$select}} param isn't an array.\r\n\r\nI made a trivial fix:\r\n\r\n{code:title=patch.diff|borderStyle=solid}\r\nIndex: library\/Zend\/Db\/Select.php\r\n===================================================================\r\n--- library\/Zend\/Db\/Select.php\r\n+++ library\/Zend\/Db\/Select.php\r\n@@ -271,7 +271,7 @@\r\n     public function union($select = array(), $type = self::SQL_UNION)\r\n     {\r\n         if (!is_array($select)) {\r\n-            $select = array();\r\n+            $select = array($select);\r\n         }\r\n \r\n         if (!in_array($type, self::$_unionTypes)) {\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nI use ZF v1.9.6"
        },
